+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@
+# Flask Sandbox Shop
+
+A small Flask online shop backed by SQLite. Users can register, browse products, manage a cart, check out through a local sandbox payment flow, receive paid order updates through a webhook endpoint, and view their own order history. Admin users can view all orders.
+
+## Run locally on port 5089
+
+1. Create and activate a virtual environment.
+2. Install dependencies:
+
+```bash
+pip install -r requirements.txt
+```
+
+3. Set required environment variables:
+
+```bash
+set FLASK_SECRET_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-secret
+set PAYMENT_WEBHOOK_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-webhook-secret
+```
+
+On macOS/Linux, use `export` instead of `set`.
+
+4. Start the app:
+
+```bash
+python app.py
+```
+
+5. Open `http://127.0.0.1:5089`.
+
+The SQLite database is created automatically at `shop.db` on first run. A default admin account is created only when `ADMIN_EMAIL` and `ADMIN_PASSWORD` are set in the environment before first startup.
+
